description: Public Policy Research Centre report accuses LDF govt of financial mismanagement in Kerala, leading to rising deficits, public debt, and challenges in various sectors like agriculture. BJP members released the report.

description: Pregnant woman forced to give birth outside Kanwatia Hospital due to lack of permanent obstetrics unit. SMS Medical College rotating unit affects care quality. Gangori Hospital has dedicated unit. Efforts made to improve facilities.
title: Hosp conducts 150 deliveries a month without gynaec dept

description: India faces drought in 125 districts as per SPEI data by IMD, Pune, impacting agriculture and water resources. States like Andhra Pradesh, Arunachal Pradesh, Gujarat, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Uttarakhand, Tamil Nadu affected. El Nino effect observed in some districts.
title: Drought crisis: 125 districts affected by severe dry conditions

description: A vehicle carrying five foreign nationals was targeted in a suicide attack in Karachi's Landhi area on Friday. Senior Superintendent of Police (SSP) Malir, Tariq Mastoi, noted that the assault also led to the deaths of two terrorists involved in the attack and caused damage to another vehicle nearby. The nationalities of the victims have not been disclosed yet.
title: 2 dead in suicide attack on vehicle carrying Japanese nationals in Karachi

description: MrBeast challenges T-Series' top spot on YouTube, gaining ground with 252M subscribers. T-Series, at 262M, invokes nationalism to rally Indian viewers. The competition intensifies as MrBeast closes the subscriber gap, aiming for the number one position.
title: Why T-Series is evoking Gulshan Kumar's message ‘against’ Mr Beast

description: Ashutosh Sharma's explosive batting almost led Punjab Kings to victory against Mumbai Indians in the IPL on Thursday. Despite his valiant effort, MI emerged victorious by nine runs. Punjab's chase of 193 to win was in disarray at 77/6 when Ashutosh walked into the middle and his 61 off just 28 balls almost stole a victory. Hardik Pandya and Sam Curran praised Ashutosh's remarkable innings.
title: Watch: Bumrah can be swept for six, Ashutosh shows how

description: Telangana faces rural distress as 15.60 lakh jobseekers surge under MGNREGS, doubling from last year. Amid elections, officials manage distress in dry conditions with districts like Vikarabad, Adilabad, Nirmal having high jobseekers.
title: Amid dry conditions, rural distress rising in Telangana

description: Google has unveiled a new Doodle to commemorate the start of the 2024 Lok Sabha elections, which began in India on Friday. The Google Doodle, which replaces the iconic "Google" logo on the search engine's homepage, features an uplifted index finger marked with indelible ink, symbolizing the essence of Indian elections.
title: Google Doodle marks start of Lok Sabha elections 2024

description: Karnataka Congress prioritizes local issues over national narrative for success in the upcoming Lok Sabha elections. Factors like candidate popularity and BJP internal dynamics play a crucial role in shaping the electoral landscape.
title: Local flavour to thwart BJP’s national campaign in Karnataka

description: Rohit Sharma supportsed neutral Test venue against Pakistan and praised their bowlers. Last year, India refused to travel to Pakistan for the Asia Cup and all of their games were rescheduled in Sri Lanka instead. Next year's ICC Champions Trophy - slated to be hosted by Pakistan - will likely be another sticking point. The last Test between India and Pakistan was played in December 2007 at Bengaluru's M Chinnaswamy Stadium.
title: Rohit Sharma bats for India-Pakistan Tests on neutral soil

description: Fayaz Kondikoppa fatally stabbed MCA student Neha Hiremath at BVB campus. Neha succumbed on the way to KIMS Hospital. Security measures will be enhanced at the campus, as per vice-chancellor Ashok Shettar.
title: Student dies after stalker stabs her on campus

description: LS elections in Maharashtra witness intense competition with top contenders like Piyush Goyal, Vinod Ghosalkar, Ashish Shelar, Varsha Gaikwad, Rahul Shewale, Anil Desai, Milind Deora, Arvind Sawant, Sudhir Mungantiwar, and Pratibha Dhanorkar across various constituencies.
title: Mahasangram: Two Senas, two NCPs, too confusing?

description: Mohammed Khalid, from Belni village, Bhatkal taluk, stuck in Tayma village for 4 years due to a road-accident case, seeks crowdfunding, appeals to Indian govt for help as a daily labourer.
title: Unable to pay Rs7 lakh fine, man confined to Saudi village for 4 yrs

description: Iran's Fars news agency reported an explosion at an airport in the city of Isafahan, but the cause was not immediately clear. Isfahan province is home to several Iranian nuclear facilities, including the Natanz uranium enrichment center. Iran launched a retaliatory strike over the weekend, deploying hundreds of drones and missiles after a suspected Israeli attack on its embassy compound in Syria.
title: Flights diverted in Iran as Israel launches strike: Key points

description: Ex fatally stabbed by mother's retaliation. Anusha filed harassment complaint. Bengaluru incident involves event management, Sarakki Park, caregiver, Hoysala patrol, autopsy, affair, stab wounds, and written assurance.
title: Man kills ex-gf in B'luru park, her mom bludgeons him to death

description: Ankit Dakhane and Mamta Chiniya, telecom engineers at IOCL, embark on separate MBA journeys at IIMA and IIMB. The couple values the diverse peer networks and rigorous academics of their simultaneous studies.
title: Husband-wife from same PSU conquer IIM-A & IIM-B
After COVID, WHO defines disease spread 'through air'

description: OTT platforms reduce content spending post-mergers for profitability. Netflix and Amazon Prime lead in content expenditure. Online video investments have tripled since the pandemic, with a focus on live sports.
title: Why viewers may see new series on Netflix more than desi companies

description: It took the mighty Brian Lara ten long years to surpass his own record of 375 and go down in history as the first batsman to ever score a 400 - a number that has dominated the political discourse in the Lok Sabha elections. As a nation that loves cricket as much as elections, parallels between the two are inevitable.
title: BJP bets big on ‘Modi ki guarantee’ in south

description: KL Rahul, LSG skipper, strives for T20 World Cup selection by excelling in middle-order/wicket-keeping. Trying to break into India's top three now seems like bringing down the Great Wall of China as skipper Rohit, Yashasvi Jaiswal, Virat Kohli and Suryakumar Yadav have locked in those spots. That begs the question, should Rahul just focus on being the destructive opening batter that he was when he was not leading teams in the IPL?
title: T20 World Cup: What is the best spot for KL Rahul?
Bullet to ballot: Manipur begins uneasy journey

description: Rohit Sharma and Shikhar Dhawan, famed Indian cricket opening duo, displayed camaraderie before an IPL match. Ashutosh Sharma's valiant effort almost secured victory for Punjab, but Mumbai Indians emerged victorious, climbing to 7th place while Punjab dropped to 9th in the points table.
title: Watch: Rohit Sharma and Shikhar Dhawan share a warm hug
